This topic describes how you can delete the Azure resources associated with
an <%= vars.ops_manager_first %> deployment. The fastest way to remove resources is to delete the
resource group, or resource groups, associated with your <%= vars.ops_manager %> on Azure installation.

## Delete the resource group

To delete a resource group:

1. Go to the [Azure Portal](https://portal.azure.com/).

1. Within your subscription, click **Resource Groups**.

1. Click the resource group you wish to delete.

1. In the details pane for the resource group, click the trash can icon. Review the information in the
confirmation pane before you proceed.

1. To confirm deletion, type in the resource group name and click **Delete**.

For more information about managing resource groups in Azure, see
the [Azure documentation](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-resource-manager/resource-group-portal).
